    {
      "id": "narrative-story-overview",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Narrative / Story Nodeset",
      "position": {
        "x": 0,
        "y": -430
      },
      "width": 500,
      "height": 320,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Narrative / Story Nodeset\n\nCandidate types from the source board:\n- `character`\n- `location`\n- `event`\n- `scene`\n- `faction`\n- `artifact`\n- `motif`\n- `timeline-beat`\n- `relationship-note`\n\nThe implementation question is whether Twilite should model authored story structure directly or only support it indirectly through generic graph primitives.",
